s":"4.2","d":1,"cat":"geometry","topic":"Geometrical constructions","qtype":"geometrical constructions","g":"mixed","src":"0580/11/O/N/25 Q05","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"In triangle $ABC$, $AB = 8$\\,cm and $BC = 6.4$\\,cm.\n\nUsing a ruler and compasses only, construct triangle $ABC$.\n\nLeave in your construction arcs.\n\nThe line $AC$ has been drawn for you.","parts":[],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"draw"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper11-Q06","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper11","qnum":6,"marks":1,"topics":["Geometry","Transformations and vectors"],"s":"4.5","d":1,"cat":"geometry","topic":"Symmetry","qtype":"symmetry","g":"mixed","src":"0580/11/O/N/25 Q06","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Shade **one** square so that the diagram has rotational symmetry of order 4.","parts":[],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"draw"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper11-Q07","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper11","qnum":7,"marks":2,"topics":["Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.7","d":1,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Sequences","qtype":"sequences","g":"sequence","src":"0580/11/O/N/25 Q07","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"These are the first four terms of a sequence.\n\n$$9 \\quad 5 \\quad 1 \\quad -3$$\n\n(a) Find the next term.\n\n(b) Explain how you worked out your answer.\n\n...\n\n...","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":1},{"label":"(b)","marks":1}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"explain"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper11-Q08","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper11","qnum":8,"marks":2,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.6","d":1,"cat":"number","topic":"The four operations","qtype":"four operations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/11/O/N/25 Q08","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"$$p = 3q - 2r$$\n\nWork out the value of $q$ when $p = 50$ and $r = 5$.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate","answer":{"type":"number","prefix":"$q$ ="}},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper11-Q09","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper11","qnum":9,"marks":3,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.6","d":1,"cat":"number","topic":"The four operations","qtype":"four operations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/11/O/N/25 Q09","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"(a) Shade \\quad$\\dfrac{3}{4}$ \\quad of this grid.\n\n(b) Work out 15\\% of 80.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":1},{"label":"(b)","marks":2}],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"draw"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper11-Q10","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper11","qnum":10,"marks":3,"topics":["Statistics"],"s":"9.4","d":1,"cat":"statistics","topic":"Statistical charts and diagrams","qtype":"statistical charts","g":"mixed","src":"0580/11/O/N/25 Q10","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"The bar chart shows the number of books sold in a shop in each of five months.\n\n(a) 4 books were sold in August.\n\nComplete the bar chart.\n\n(b) Calculate the mean number of books sold in the six months.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":1},{"label":"(b)","marks":2}],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"complete"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper11-Q11","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper11","qnum":11,"marks":2,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.6","d":1,"cat":"number","topic":"The four operations","qtype":"four operations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/11/O/N/25 Q11","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"The temperature at midnight is $-2\\,^\\circ\\text{C}$.\n\nThe temperature at noon is $5\\,^\\circ\\text{C}$.\n\n(a) Find the difference between these temperatures.\n\n(b) The temperature at 9\\,am is $8\\,^\\circ\\text{C}$ higher than the temperature at midnight.\n\nWork out the temperature at 9\\,am.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":1,"answer":{"type":"number","suffix":"°C$"}},{"label":"(b)","marks":1,"answer":{"type":"number","suffix":"°C$"}}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper11-Q12","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper11","qnum":12,"marks":3,"topics":["Mensuration"],"s":"5.2","d":1,"cat":"mensuration","topic":"Area and perimeter","qtype":"area and perimeter","g":"mixed","src":"0580/11/O/N/25 Q12","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Complete the net of this cuboid on the 1\\,cm$^2$ grid.\n\nOne face has been drawn for you.","parts":[],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"complete"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper11-Q13","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper11","qnum":13,"marks":5,"topics":["Geometry"],"s":"4.3","d":1,"cat":"geometry","topic":"Scale drawings and bearings","qtype":"scale drawings and bearings","g":"mixed","src":"0580/11/O/N/25 Q13","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"The scale drawing shows the positions of town $A$ and town $B$.\n\nThe scale is 1 centimetre represents 10 kilometres.\n\n(a) Work out the actual distance from town $A$ to town $B$.\n\n(b) Measure the bearing of town $B$ from town $A$.\n\n(c) Town $C$ is 45\\,km from town $A$ on a bearing of $310^\\circ$.\n\nOn the scale drawing, mark the position of town $C$.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":2,"answer":{"type":"number","suffix":"km"}},{"label":"(b)","marks":1,"answer":{"type":"number","suffix":"°"}},{"label":"(c)","marks":2}],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper11-Q14","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper11","qnum":14,"marks":4,"topics":["Statistics"],"s":"9.4","d":1,"cat":"statistics","topic":"Statistical charts and diagrams","qtype":"statistical charts","g":"mixed","src":"0580/11/O/N/25 Q14","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"These are the ages, in months, of each of 12 children.\n\n$$11 \\quad 27 \\quad 8 \\quad 10 \\quad 26 \\quad 17 \\quad 28 \\quad 12 \\quad 9 \\quad 13 \\quad 22 \\quad 12$$\n\n(a) Complete the stem-and-leaf diagram to show this information.\n\n(b) Find the number of children over 2 years old.\n\n(c) Show that the median is 12.5.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":2},{"label":"(b)","marks":1},{"label":"(c)","marks":1}],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"analyse","cmd":"show"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper11-Q15","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper11","qnum":15,"marks":3,"topics":["Geometry"],"s":"4.6","d":1,"cat":"geometry","topic":"Angles","qtype":"angle calculations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/11/O/N/25 Q15","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"$ABC$ is a straight line and $ABD$ is an isosceles triangle.\n\nWork out the value of $x$.","parts":[],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate","answer":{"type":"number","prefix":"$x$ ="}},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper11-Q16","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper11","qnum":16,"marks":6,"topics":["Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.10","d":1,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Graphs of functions","qtype":"graphs of functions","g":"function","src":"0580/11/O/N/25 Q16","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"(a) Complete the table of values for \\quad $y = \\dfrac{9}{x}$.\n\n(b) On the grid, draw the graph of \\quad $y = \\dfrac{9}{x}$ \\quad for $-4.5 \\leqslant x \\leqslant -1$ \\quad and \\quad $1 \\leqslant x \\leqslant 4.5$.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":2},{"label":"(b)","marks":4}],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"draw"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper11-Q17","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper11","qnum":17,"marks":2,"topics":["Number","Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.2","d":1,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Algebraic manipulation","qtype":"algebraic manipulation","g":"mixed","src":"0580/11/O/N/25 Q17","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"(a) Write down a prime number between 20 and 30.\n\n(b) Simplify \\quad $(\\sqrt{9})^2$.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":1},{"label":"(b)","marks":1}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"simplify"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper11-Q18","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper11","qnum":18,"marks":2,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.4","d":1,"cat":"number","topic":"Fractions, decimals, percentages","qtype":"fractions, decimals, percentages","g":"mixed","src":"0580/11/O/N/25 Q18","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Work out \\quad $\\dfrac{11}{18} - \\dfrac{2}{9}$.\n\nGive your answer as a fraction in its simplest form.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper11-Q19","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper11","qnum":19,"marks":2,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.9","d":1,"cat":"number","topic":"Estimation","qtype":"estimation and rounding","g":"mixed","src":"0580/11/O/N/25 Q19","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"By writing each number in the calculation correct to 1 significant figure, find an estimate for the value of\n\n$$\\dfrac{5.3 \\times 19.5}{2.49}.$$","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper11-Q20","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper11","qnum":20,"marks":2,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.6","d":1,"cat":"number","topic":"The four operations","qtype":"four operations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/11/O/N/25 Q20","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Some students take a test.\n\n75 of the students pass the test.\n\nThis is \\quad$\\dfrac{3}{5}$ \\quad of the students who take the test.\n\nWork out how many students take the test.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper11-Q21","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper11","qnum":21,"marks":5,"topics":["Transformations and vectors"],"s":"7.1","d":1,"cat":"vectors","topic":"Transformations","qtype":"transformations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/11/O/N/25 Q21","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Shapes $A$ and $B$ are shown on the grid.\n\n(a) Describe fully the **single** transformation that maps shape $A$ onto shape $B$.\n\n...\n\n...\n\n...\n\n(b) Draw the image of shape $A$ after a reflection in the line $y = -1$.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":3},{"label":"(b)","marks":2}],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"describe"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper11-Q22","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper11","qnum":22,"marks":3,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.6","d":1,"cat":"number","topic":"The four operations","qtype":"four operations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/11/O/N/25 Q22","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"(a) Sunita makes 24 chocolate cookies.\n\nWork out how much flour she needs.\n\n(b) Albie has 28\\,g of cocoa.\n\nDoes he have enough cocoa to make 18 cookies?\n\nExplain how you decide.\n\n...\n\n...","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":1,"answer":{"type":"number","suffix":"g"}},{"label":"(b)","marks":2}],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"explain"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper11-Q23","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper11","qnum":23,"marks":2,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.6","d":1,"cat":"number","topic":"The four operations","qtype":"four operations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/11/O/N/25 Q23","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"(a) $$a^8 \\times a^x = a^{15}$$\n\nFind the value of $x$.\n\n(b) $$(b^7)^y = b^{21}$$\n\nFind the value of $y$.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":1,"answer":{"type":"number","prefix":"$x$ ="}},{"label":"(b)","marks":1,"answer":{"type":"number","prefix":"$y$ ="}}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper11-Q24","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper11","qnum":24,"marks":4,"topics":["Number","Probability"],"s":"1.2","d":1,"cat":"number","topic":"Sets","qtype":"sets and Venn diagrams","g":"mixed","src":"0580/11/O/N/25 Q24","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"$\\mathcal{E} = \\{ \\text{students in a year group} \\}$ \n\n$H = \\{ \\text{students who study History} \\}$ \n\n$G = \\{ \\text{students who study Geography} \\}$\n\n80 students are in the year group. \n\n40 students study History.\n\n(a) Complete the Venn diagram.\n\n(b) Find $\\mathrm{n}(G)$.\n\n(c) A student is chosen at random.\n\nWork out the probability that the student does not study History and does not study Geography.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":2},{"label":"(b)","marks":1},{"label":"(c)","marks":1}],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"complete"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper11-Q25","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper11","qnum":25,"marks":2,"topics":["Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.2","d":1,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Algebraic manipulation","qtype":"algebraic manipulation","g":"mixed","src":"0580/11/O/N/25 Q25","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Expand and simplify.\n\n$$(x + 3)(x - 2)$$","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"simplify"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper11-Q26","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper11","qnum":26,"marks":1,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.8","d":1,"cat":"number","topic":"Standard form","qtype":"standard form","g":"mixed","src":"0580/11/O/N/25 Q26","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Write $1.753 \\times 10^8$ as an ordinary number.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"write"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper11-Q27","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper11","qnum":27,"marks":3,"topics":["Geometry","Mensuration"],"s":"4.6","d":1,"cat":"geometry","topic":"Angles","qtype":"angle calculations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/11/O/N/25 Q27","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"The diagram shows a semicircle.\n\nThe radius of the semicircle is 8\\,cm.\n\nFind the perimeter of the semicircle.\n\nGive your answer in terms of $\\pi$ in its simplest form.","parts":[],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find","answer":{"type":"number","suffix":"cm"}},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper11-Q28","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper11","qnum":28,"marks":3,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.6","d":1,"cat":"number","topic":"The four operations","qtype":"four operations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/11/O/N/25 Q28","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Work out $8 \\frac{2}{3} \\div 1 \\frac{5}{8}$.\n\nGive your answer as a mixed number in its simplest form.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper11-Q29","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper11","qnum":29,"marks":5,"topics":["Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.5","d":1,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Equations","qtype":"equations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/11/O/N/25 Q29","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Jim buys 15 apples and 10 pears for \\$42.50.\n\nLi buys 4 apples and 5 pears for \\$16.\n\nWrite down a pair of simultaneous equations and solve them to find the cost of one apple and the cost of one pear.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"solve","answer":{"type":"multiline","lines":2,"layout":"column","template":